eriRouterSubscriberActiveMib.name: eriRouterSubscriberActiveMib

revisions.description: Added eriRouterSubsActiveSessionNx entry to eriRouterSubsActiveTable Added eriRouterSubsActiveAddrInt entry to eriRouterSubsActiveIpTable

Modified below attribute names of table eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeTable for better readability. eriRouterSubsServiceIPv4VolumeOctetsIn --> eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumeOctetsIn eriRouterSubsServiceIPv4VolumeOctetsOut --> eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumeOctetsOut eriRouterSubsServiceIPv4VolumePktsIn --> eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumePktsIn eriRouterSubsServiceIPv4VolumePktsOut --> eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumePktsOut eriRouterSubsServiceIPv6VolumeOctetsIn --> eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumeOctetsIn eriRouterSubsServiceIPv6VolumeOctetsOut --> eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumeOctetsOut eriRouterSubsServiceIPv6VolumePktsIn --> eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumePktsIn eriRouterSubsServiceIPv6VolumePktsOut --> eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumePktsOut
Updated RBN/rbn/Rbn as ERICSSON-ROUTER/eriRouter/EriRouter to migrate RBN MIB to ERICSSON MIB.
Changed the following not-accessible objects to read-only eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrType eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddr eriRouterSubsActiveIpPfxLen

Add eriRouterSubsIPv4OctetsSent, eriRouterSubsIPv4OctetsReceived, eriRouterSubsIPv6OctetsSent, eriRouterSubsIPv6OctetsReceived, eriRouterSubsIPv4PktsSent, eriRouterSubsIPv4PktsReceived, eriRouterSubsIPv6PktsSent, eriRouterSubsIPv6PktsReceived, eriRouterSubsIPv4McastOctetsSent, eriRouterSubsIPv4McastOctetsReceived, eriRouterSubsIPv6McastOctetsSent, eriRouterSubsIPv6McastOctetsReceived, eriRouterSubsIPv4McastPktsSent, eriRouterSubsIPv4McastPktsReceived, eriRouterSubsIPv6McastPktsSent, eriRouterSubsIPv6McastPktsReceived to EriRouterSubsStatsEntry table eriRouterSubsServiceIPv4VolumeOctetsIn, eriRouterSubsServiceIPv4VolumeOctetsOut, eriRouterSubsServiceIPv6VolumeOctetsIn, eriRouterSubsServiceIPv6VolumeOctetsOut, eriRouterSubsServiceIPv4VolumePktsIn, eriRouterSubsServiceIPv4VolumePktsOut, eriRouterSubsServiceIPv6VolumePktsIn, eriRouterSubsServiceIPv6VolumePktsOut to EriRouterSubsServiceVolumeEntry table

Add eriRouterSubsMaxSupportedSessions, eriRouterSubsLicensedSessions, eriRouterSubsActiveSessions, and eriRouterSubsCapacityPercentageUsed. Defined eriRouterSubsCompliance5 and eriRouterSubsLicenseGroup for compliance. Deprecated eriRouterSubsCompliance4 and obsoleted eriRouterSubsCompliance3.
Add eriRouterSubsConfigErrorEvent notification along with the associated objects. Defined eriRouterSubsNotifyObjectGroup and eriRouterSubsNotifyGroup for compliance.

Add eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeTable and eriRouterSubsServicesTable along with associated objects. Defined eriRouterSubsCompliance4 and eriRouterSubsServicesGroup for compliance. Deprecated eriRouterSubsCompliance3 and obsoleted eriRouterSubsCompliance2.
Add eriRouterSubsActiveNasPortType and eriRouterSubsActiveMediumType to EriRouterSubsActiveEntry. Update conformance objects appropriately.
Add objects eriRouterSubsReauthName and eriRouterSubsReauthSessionId. These objects supercede the objects defined in the ERICSSON-ROUTER-SUBSCRIBER-REAUTH-MIB.

Add eriRouterSubsActiveResend to eriRouterSubsActiveEntry. Add eriRouterSubsProfileCountTable with objects eriRouterSubsProfileName and eriRouterSubsProfileCount. Updated compliance and groups to reflect new objects.

eriRouterSubscriberActiveMib.contactinfo: Ericsson AB. 2755 Augustine Drive Santa Clara, CA 95054 USA Phone: +1 408 750 5000 Fax: +1 408 750 5599
eriRouterSubscriberActiveMib.description: Defines the objects necessary to support the management of active subscribers. All mib objects, except eriRouterSubsCntxtCountTable, defined in the module are viewed within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3).

eriRouterSubsActiveTable.name: eriRouterSubsActiveTable
eriRouterSubsActiveTable.description: This table contains subscriber sessions which have been authenticated on an circuit.

eriRouterSubsActiveEntry.name: eriRouterSubsActiveEntry
eriRouterSubsActiveEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterSubsActiveTable.

eriRouterSubsActiveName.name: eriRouterSubsActiveName
eriRouterSubsActiveName.description: The name identifying this entry. An entry configured by other means may have been given a name whose length is greater than 80. Names which exceed this length are not accessible via SNMP operations.

eriRouterSubsActiveSessionId.name: eriRouterSubsActiveSessionId
eriRouterSubsActiveSessionId.reference: Rigney, C., RADIUS Accounting, RFC 2866, June 2000
eriRouterSubsActiveSessionId.description: A value that uniquely identifies an active subscriber session. If RADIUS is being used to configure/authenticate subscribers, this value will appear in the RADIUS Acct-Session-Id attribute.

eriRouterSubsActiveCircuitDescr.name: eriRouterSubsActiveCircuitDescr
eriRouterSubsActiveCircuitDescr.description: A string which provides identifying information (e.g slot/port) of the circuit the subscriber is using.

eriRouterSubsActiveStartTime.name: eriRouterSubsActiveStartTime
eriRouterSubsActiveStartTime.description: The time when the subscriber became active.

eriRouterSubsActiveClear.name: eriRouterSubsActiveClear
eriRouterSubsActiveClear.description: Setting this value to 'true' will clear the active subscriber session. In the case of PPP, the PPP state machinery attempts to renegotiate and re-authenticate a new session with the remote peer on the circuit. In the case of RFC 1483 encapsulated circuits the session is brought down and then back up and an attempt is made to re-authenticate the subscriber. An SNMP get operation always returns 'false'

eriRouterSubsActiveResend.name: eriRouterSubsActiveResend
eriRouterSubsActiveResend.description: Setting this value to 'true' will cause a resend of the Radius acct-start packet. An SNMP get operation always returns 'false'

eriRouterSubsActiveNasPortType.name: eriRouterSubsActiveNasPortType
eriRouterSubsActiveNasPortType.reference: Rigney, C., Rubens, A., Simpson, W., and Willens, S., Remote Authentication Dial In User Service (RADIUS), RFC 2865, June 2000
eriRouterSubsActiveNasPortType.description: The RADIUS attribute NAS-Port-Type which indicates the type of the physical port which is authenticating the user.

eriRouterSubsActiveMediumType.name: eriRouterSubsActiveMediumType
eriRouterSubsActiveMediumType.description: The medium type of the NAS-Port.

eriRouterSubsActiveResendSvcAcct.name: eriRouterSubsActiveResendSvcAcct
eriRouterSubsActiveResendSvcAcct.description: Setting this value to 'true' will cause a resend of the Radius acct-start packet for all services associated with the active subscriber session. An SNMP get operation always returns 'false'

eriRouterSubsActiveSessionNx.name: eriRouterSubsActiveSessionNx
eriRouterSubsActiveSessionNx.description: This object returns the same value as eriRouterSubsActiveSessionId, Only difference is it's accessible object.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpTable.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpTable
eriRouterSubsActiveIpTable.description: This table contains IP addresses used by active subscribers.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpEntry.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpEntry
eriRouterSubsActiveIpEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterSubsActiveIpTable.

eriRouterSubsActiveAddr.name: eriRouterSubsActiveAddr
eriRouterSubsActiveAddr.description: The host IP address of the active subscriber.

eriRouterSubsActiveAddrInt.name: eriRouterSubsActiveAddrInt
eriRouterSubsActiveAddrInt.description: The host IP address of the active subscriber. The value of this object is limited to the IPv4 address. Hence, mustbe used only when eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrType is of type v4.

eriRouterSubsActiveSessionTable.name: eriRouterSubsActiveSessionTable
eriRouterSubsActiveSessionTable.description: This table contains active subscriber sessions which have been authenticated on an circuit.

eriRouterSubsActiveSessionEntry.name: eriRouterSubsActiveSessionEntry
eriRouterSubsActiveSessionEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterSubsActiveSessionTable.

eriRouterSubsActiveSessionSubscriberName.name: eriRouterSubsActiveSessionSubscriberName
eriRouterSubsActiveSessionSubscriberName.description: The subscriber name associated with this session.

eriRouterSubsActiveSessionPointer.name: eriRouterSubsActiveSessionPointer
eriRouterSubsActiveSessionPointer.description: A pointer to the row in eriRouterSubsActiveTable to which this session belongs. May be {0 0} if there is no such row.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrTable.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrTable
eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrTable.description: This table contains IPv4/IPv6 addresses used by active subscriber sessions.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrEntry.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrEntry
eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrTable.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddr.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddr
eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddr.reference: [RFC4291] IP Version 6 Addressing Architectur [RFC4632] Classless Inter-domain Routing (CIDR): The Internet Address Assignment and Aggregation Plan
eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddr.description: The address prefix. The address type of this object is specified in eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrType. The length of this object is the standard length for objects of that type (4 or 16 bytes). Any bits after eriRouterSubsActiveIpPfxLen must be zero.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpPfxLen.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpPfxLen
eriRouterSubsActiveIpPfxLen.description: The prefix length associated with this prefix. For IPv4 active subscriber session, the prefix length is always 32.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrDescr.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrDescr
eriRouterSubsActiveIpAddrDescr.description: Human readable textual format of IP address.

eriRouterSubsClearSubscriberName.name: eriRouterSubsClearSubscriberName
eriRouterSubsClearSubscriberName.description: Setting this object to the subscriber name will clear all the sessions associated with the subscriber. In the case of PPP circuit, the PPP state machinery attempts to renegotiate and re-authenticate a new session with the remote peer on the circuit. In the case of RFC 1483 and RFC 1490 encapsulated circuits the circuit is brought down and then back up and an attempt is made to re-authenticate the subscriber bound to the circuit. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

eriRouterSubsClearSessionId.name: eriRouterSubsClearSessionId
eriRouterSubsClearSessionId.description: A set of this object will clear the subscriber session identified by this value. In the case of PPP circuit, the PPP state machinery attempts to renegotiate and re-authenticate a new session with the remote peer on the circuit. In the case of RFC 1483 and RFC 1490 encapsulated circuits the circuit is brought down and then back up and an attempt is made to re-authenticate the subscriber bound to the circuit. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

eriRouterSubsBounceName.name: eriRouterSubsBounceName
eriRouterSubsBounceName.description: Each circuit using CLIPS encapsulation used by the named subscriber is brought down and immediately recreated using the RADIUS Access- Accept attributes. Any other circuit encapsulation type is cleared. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

eriRouterSubsBounceSessionId.name: eriRouterSubsBounceSessionId
eriRouterSubsBounceSessionId.description: The circuit using CLIPS encapsulation identified by the RADIUS Acct-Session-Id is brought down and immediately recreated using the RADIUS Access-Accept attributes. Any other circuit encapsulation type is cleared. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

eriRouterSubsReauthRadiusIndex.name: eriRouterSubsReauthRadiusIndex
eriRouterSubsReauthRadiusIndex.description: An unsigned integer identifying a set of subscribers defined at the RADIUS server which are to be re-authorized. The source of this value and the set of subscribers to be re-authorized are defined outside the context of this mib module. An get of this attribute returns 0.

eriRouterSubsReauthRadiusID.name: eriRouterSubsReauthRadiusID
eriRouterSubsReauthRadiusID.description: An octet string identifying a set of subscribers defined at the RADIUS server which are to be re-authorized. The source of this value and the set of subscribers to be re-authorized are defined outside the context of this mib module. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

eriRouterSubsReauthName.name: eriRouterSubsReauthName
eriRouterSubsReauthName.description: Used to reauthorize all of the active sessions associated with the given subscriber in the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3). This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

eriRouterSubsReauthSessionId.name: eriRouterSubsReauthSessionId
eriRouterSubsReauthSessionId.description: Used to reauthorize the active session identified by the value of this object and the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3). This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

eriRouterSubsClearReason.name: eriRouterSubsClearReason
eriRouterSubsClearReason.description: An unsigned integer value which may be included in the set request for eriRouterSubsClearSubscriberName, eriRouterSubsClearSessionId, eriRouterSubsBounceName, eriRouterSubsBounceSessionId, or any other objects define under the eriRouterSubsClear OID node. The use of this object value is implementation dependent. This object returns 0 when queried.

eriRouterSubsCntxtCountTable.name: eriRouterSubsCntxtCountTable
eriRouterSubsCntxtCountTable.description: This table contains counts of active subscribers by context name. Unlike any of the other tables in this mib module, all rows in this table are accessible when the context 'local' is specified in the snmp message, unless restricted by entries in the vacmAccessTable. Snmp requests using other contexts shall return only the row which matches the context.

eriRouterSubsCntxtCountEntry.name: eriRouterSubsCntxtCountEntry
eriRouterSubsCntxtCountEntry.description: The conceptual row containing the count of active subscribers for each context.

eriRouterSubsCntxtCount.name: eriRouterSubsCntxtCount
eriRouterSubsCntxtCount.description: The count of active subscribers with either IPv4 or IPv6 or both stack UP.

eriRouterSubsCntxtIp4OnlyCount.name: eriRouterSubsCntxtIp4OnlyCount
eriRouterSubsCntxtIp4OnlyCount.description: The count of IPv4 active subscribers which are authorized for only IPv4 protocol stack. This counter does not include subscribers authorized for dual IPv4/IPv6 protocol stack.

eriRouterSubsCntxtIp6OnlyCount.name: eriRouterSubsCntxtIp6OnlyCount
eriRouterSubsCntxtIp6OnlyCount.description: The count of IPv6 active subscribers which are authorized for only IPv6 protocol stack. This counter does not include subscribers authorized for dual IPv4/IPv6 protocol stack.

eriRouterSubsCntxtDualCount.name: eriRouterSubsCntxtDualCount
eriRouterSubsCntxtDualCount.description: The count of active subscribers which are authorized for both IPv4 and IPv6 for the context. At any time either one or both stacks may be UP.

eriRouterSubsCntxtLacCount.name: eriRouterSubsCntxtLacCount
eriRouterSubsCntxtLacCount.description: The count of active LAC subscribers.

eriRouterSubsEncapsCountTable.name: eriRouterSubsEncapsCountTable
eriRouterSubsEncapsCountTable.description: This table contains counts of active subscribers by encapsulation type.

eriRouterSubsEncapsCountEntry.name: eriRouterSubsEncapsCountEntry
eriRouterSubsEncapsCountEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterSubsEncapsCountTable.

eriRouterSubsEncapsulationType.name: eriRouterSubsEncapsulationType
eriRouterSubsEncapsulationType.description: This object identifies the type of encapsulation the subscriber is using. Note that 'ppp' includes all types of supported ppp, excluding pppoe.

eriRouterSubsEncapsCount.name: eriRouterSubsEncapsCount
eriRouterSubsEncapsCount.description: The count of active subscribers for the encapsulation type.

eriRouterSubsStatsTable.name: eriRouterSubsStatsTable
eriRouterSubsStatsTable.description: This table contains counters for individual circuits.

eriRouterSubsStatsEntry.name: eriRouterSubsStatsEntry
eriRouterSubsStatsEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterSubsStatsTable.

eriRouterSubsOctetsSent.name: eriRouterSubsOctetsSent
eriRouterSubsOctetsSent.description: The number of octets sent by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsOctetsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsOctetsReceived
eriRouterSubsOctetsReceived.description: The number of octets received by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsPktsSent.name: eriRouterSubsPktsSent
eriRouterSubsPktsSent.description: The number of packets sent by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsPktsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsPktsReceived
eriRouterSubsPktsReceived.description: The number of packets received by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsXmitOctetsDropped.name: eriRouterSubsXmitOctetsDropped
eriRouterSubsXmitOctetsDropped.description: The number of octets dropped by the circuit before transmission.

eriRouterSubsXmitPktsDropped.name: eriRouterSubsXmitPktsDropped
eriRouterSubsXmitPktsDropped.description: The number of packets dropped by the circuit before transmission.

eriRouterSubsMcastOctetsSent.name: eriRouterSubsMcastOctetsSent
eriRouterSubsMcastOctetsSent.description: The number of multicast octets sent by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsMcastOctetsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsMcastOctetsReceived
eriRouterSubsMcastOctetsReceived.description: The number of multicast octets received by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsMcastPktsSent.name: eriRouterSubsMcastPktsSent
eriRouterSubsMcastPktsSent.description: The number of multicast packets sent by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsMcastPktsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsMcastPktsReceived
eriRouterSubsMcastPktsReceived.description: The number of multicast packets received by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsIPv4OctetsSent.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4OctetsSent
eriRouterSubsIPv4OctetsSent.description: The number of IPv4 octets sent by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsIPv4OctetsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4OctetsReceived
eriRouterSubsIPv4OctetsReceived.description: The number of IPv4 octets received by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsIPv6OctetsSent.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6OctetsSent
eriRouterSubsIPv6OctetsSent.description: The number of IPv6 octets sent by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsIPv6OctetsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6OctetsReceived
eriRouterSubsIPv6OctetsReceived.description: The number of IPv6 octets received by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsIPv4PktsSent.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4PktsSent
eriRouterSubsIPv4PktsSent.description: The number of IPv4 packets sent by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsIPv4PktsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4PktsReceived
eriRouterSubsIPv4PktsReceived.description: The number of IPv4 packets received by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsIPv6PktsSent.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6PktsSent
eriRouterSubsIPv6PktsSent.description: The number of IPv6 packets sent by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsIPv6PktsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6PktsReceived
eriRouterSubsIPv6PktsReceived.description: The number of IPv6 packets received by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

eriRouterSubsIPv4McastOctetsSent.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4McastOctetsSent
eriRouterSubsIPv4McastOctetsSent.description: The number of IPv4 multicast octets sent by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsIPv4McastOctetsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4McastOctetsReceived
eriRouterSubsIPv4McastOctetsReceived.description: The number of IPv4 multicast octets received by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsIPv6McastOctetsSent.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6McastOctetsSent
eriRouterSubsIPv6McastOctetsSent.description: The number of IPv6 multicast octets sent by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsIPv6McastOctetsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6McastOctetsReceived
eriRouterSubsIPv6McastOctetsReceived.description: The number of IPv6 multicast octets received by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsIPv4McastPktsSent.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4McastPktsSent
eriRouterSubsIPv4McastPktsSent.description: The number of IPv4 multicast packets sent by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsIPv4McastPktsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4McastPktsReceived
eriRouterSubsIPv4McastPktsReceived.description: The number of IPv4 multicast packets received by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsIPv6McastPktsSent.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6McastPktsSent
eriRouterSubsIPv6McastPktsSent.description: The number of IPv6 multicast packets sent by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsIPv6McastPktsReceived.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6McastPktsReceived
eriRouterSubsIPv6McastPktsReceived.description: The number of IPv6 multicast packets received by the circuit.

eriRouterSubsProfileCountTable.name: eriRouterSubsProfileCountTable
eriRouterSubsProfileCountTable.description: This table contains counts of active subscribers by encapsulation type.

eriRouterSubsProfileCountEntry.name: eriRouterSubsProfileCountEntry
eriRouterSubsProfileCountEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterSubsProfileCountTable.

eriRouterSubsProfileName.name: eriRouterSubsProfileName
eriRouterSubsProfileName.description: The profile name which applies to a set of subscribers.

eriRouterSubsProfileCount.name: eriRouterSubsProfileCount
eriRouterSubsProfileCount.description: The count of active subscribers for the profile name.

eriRouterSubsMaxSupportedSessions.name: eriRouterSubsMaxSupportedSessions
eriRouterSubsMaxSupportedSessions.description: The maximum number of active subscriber sessions that are supported on the SmartEdge router.

eriRouterSubsLicensedSessions.name: eriRouterSubsLicensedSessions
eriRouterSubsLicensedSessions.description: The number of licensed subscriber sessions on the SmartEdge router.

eriRouterSubsActiveSessions.name: eriRouterSubsActiveSessions
eriRouterSubsActiveSessions.description: The number of active subscriber sessions on the SmartEdge router.

eriRouterSubsCapacityPercentageUsed.name: eriRouterSubsCapacityPercentageUsed
eriRouterSubsCapacityPercentageUsed.description: The percentage of licensed subscriber sessions in use on the SmartEdge router. This value is computed as: if eriRouterSubsLicensedSessions equals 0 then if eriRouterSubsActiveSessions equals 0 then 0 else 100 else MIN((eriRouterSubsActiveSessions * 100)/eriRouterSubsLicensedSessions), 100).

eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeTable.name: eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeTable
eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeTable.description: This table specifies service volume information on the subscriber circuits. It contains the volume octet counts for each active subscriber session for which the service is active. All MIB objects defined in the table are viewed within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3).

eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeEntry.name: eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeEntry
eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeEntry.description: A conceptual row in the EriRouterSubsServiceVolumeTable. Each row contains the service volume limit and volume octet count for each active service session.

eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeLimitIn.name: eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeLimitIn
eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeLimitIn.description: The volume limit in kilobytes (KB) allowed for the subscriber service to input (or receive) for this subscriber. If the value is 0, then there is no limit.

eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeLimitOut.name: eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeLimitOut
eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeLimitOut.description: The volume limit in kilobytes (KB) allowed for the subscriber service to output (or transmit) for this subscriber. If the value is 0, then there is no limit.

eriRouterSubsServiceActiveTime.name: eriRouterSubsServiceActiveTime
eriRouterSubsServiceActiveTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the service became active for this subscriber. If sysUpTime is reset to zero as a result of a reinitialization of the network management (sub)system, then the values of all TimeStamp objects are also reset.

eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeOctetsIn.name: eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeOctetsIn
eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeOctetsIn.description: The subscriber session volume octets in count.

eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeOctetsOut.name: eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeOctetsOut
eriRouterSubsServiceVolumeOctetsOut.description: The subscriber session volume octets out count.

eriRouterSubsServiceVolumePktsIn.name: eriRouterSubsServiceVolumePktsIn
eriRouterSubsServiceVolumePktsIn.description: The subscriber session volume packet in count.

eriRouterSubsServiceVolumePktsOut.name: eriRouterSubsServiceVolumePktsOut
eriRouterSubsServiceVolumePktsOut.description: The subscriber session volume packet out count.

eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumeOctetsIn.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumeOctetsIn
eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumeOctetsIn.description: The subscriber session volume IPv4 octets in count.

eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumeOctetsOut.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumeOctetsOut
eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumeOctetsOut.description: The subscriber session volume IPv4 octets out count.

eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumePktsIn.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumePktsIn
eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumePktsIn.description: The subscriber session volume IPv4 packet in count.

eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumePktsOut.name: eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumePktsOut
eriRouterSubsIPv4ServiceVolumePktsOut.description: The subscriber session volume IPv4 packet out count.

eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumeOctetsIn.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumeOctetsIn
eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumeOctetsIn.description: The subscriber session volume IPv6 octets in count.

eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumeOctetsOut.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumeOctetsOut
eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumeOctetsOut.description: The subscriber session volume IPv6 octets out count.

eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumePktsIn.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumePktsIn
eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumePktsIn.description: The subscriber session volume IPv6 packet in count.

eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumePktsOut.name: eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumePktsOut
eriRouterSubsIPv6ServiceVolumePktsOut.description: The subscriber session volume IPv6 packet out count.

eriRouterSubsServicesTable.name: eriRouterSubsServicesTable
eriRouterSubsServicesTable.description: This table contains services available to subscribers.

eriRouterSubsServicesEntry.name: eriRouterSubsServicesEntry
eriRouterSubsServicesEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterSubsServicesTable.

eriRouterSubsServiceIndex.name: eriRouterSubsServiceIndex
eriRouterSubsServiceIndex.description: A unique index assigned to the entry.

eriRouterSubsServiceTag.name: eriRouterSubsServiceTag
eriRouterSubsServiceTag.description: A tag associated with the service name which may provide additional qualification to the name.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalTable.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalTable
eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalTable.description: This table contains information about the active subscribers in the system. A walk on the table with a specific context would return only those active subscribers belonging to the context. A walk on this table with context local would return all the active subscribers across all contexts in the system. A walk on this table without specifying any context would return all active subscribers across all contexts in the system. This table is supported only for IPv4 subscribers and will not be instantiated for single stack IPv6 subscriber.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalEntry.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalEntry
eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalTable.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalSessionId.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalSessionId
eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalSessionId.description: The session ID for the active subscriber. This object returns the same value as Acct-Session-ID AVP used for subscriber accounting.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalName.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalName
eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalName.description: The Username for the active subscriber. User name can be of the format name@context or name@domain.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalAddress.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalAddress
eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalAddress.description: The IPv4 address assigned to the active subscriber. For dual stack subscriber, the address of the IPv4 stack is returned.

eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalMask.name: eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalMask
eriRouterSubsActiveIpv4GlobalMask.description: The IPv4 subnet mask assigned to the active subscriber. The subnet mask is always 255.255.255.255.
